{
  "local_port": 38042,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am planning a 4 day Holiday in North India. Where can I go?",
  "response": "North India is a treasure trove of cultural, historical, and natural beauty, offering a variety of destinations for a 4-day holiday. Here are some great options based on your interests:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Delhi-Agra-Jaipur (Golden Triangle)**\n- **Day 1**: Explore Delhi\u2019s iconic landmarks like Red Fort, Qutub Minar, Humayun\u2019s Tomb, and India Gate.\n- **Day 2**: Head to Agra to visit the Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, and Mehtab Bagh.\n- **Day 3**: Travel to Jaipur and explore Amer Fort, Hawa Mahal, City Palace, and Jantar Mantar.\n- **Day 4**: Visit Albert Hall Museum, shop for traditional handicrafts, and return to Delhi.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Shimla-Manali (Himachal Pradesh)**\n- **Day 1**: Travel to Shimla and explore Mall Road, The Ridge, and Jakhoo Temple.\n- **Day 2**: Head to Manali and enjoy the scenic drive. Rest and explore local cafes.\n- **Day 3**: Visit Solang Valley, Hadimba Temple, and Old Manali.\n- **Day 4**: Take a day trip to Rohtang Pass or enjoy adventure activities like paragliding.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Rishikesh-Haridwar (Spiritual and Adventure)**\n- **Day 1**: Travel to Rishikesh and visit Triveni Ghat, Laxman Jhula, and Ram Jhula.\n- **Day 2**: Enjoy river rafting, bungee jumping, or yoga sessions.\n- **Day 3**: Travel to Haridwar and witness the Ganga Aarti at Har Ki Pauri.\n- **Day 4**: Visit Mansa Devi Temple and Chandi Devi Temple.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Udaipur-Pushkar (Rajasthan)**\n- **Day 1**: Explore Udaipur\u2019s City Palace, Lake Pichola, and Jag Mandir.\n- **Day 2**: Visit Saheliyon Ki Bari, Bagore ki Haveli, and enjoy a boat ride.\n- **Day 3**: Travel to Pushkar and visit the Brahma Temple and Pushkar Lake.\n- **Day 4**: Explore Ajmer Sharif Dargah and return.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Jim Corbett National Park-Nainital**\n- **Day 1**: Travel to Jim Corbett National Park and enjoy a safari.\n- **Day 2**: Explore the park further and relax at your resort.\n- **Day 3**: Travel to Nainital and visit Naini Lake, Naina Devi Temple, and Snow View Point.\n- **Day 4**: Explore Bhimtal and Sattal before heading back.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Amritsar-Wagah Border (Punjab)**\n- **Day 1**: Travel to Amritsar and visit the Golden Temple and Jallianwala Bagh.\n- **Day 2**: Attend the Wagah Border ceremony and explore Partition Museum.\n- **Day 3**: Visit Ram Tirath and enjoy Punjabi cuisine.\n- **Day 4**: Shop for traditional items and return.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Leh-Ladakh (Adventure and Scenic Beauty)**\n- **Day 1**: Fly to Leh and acclimatize. Visit Shanti Stupa and Leh Palace.\n- **Day 2**: Explore Nubra Valley via Khardung La Pass.\n- **Day 3**: Visit Pangong Lake and camp overnight.\n- **Day 4**: Return to Leh and fly back.\n\n---\n\nChoose a destination based on your preferences\u2014history, spirituality, adventure, or relaxation. Let me know if you\u2019d like more details about any of these options! \u2728",
  "temperature": 1.0,
